			<h3>How It Works</h3>
			<img class="one-third column" src="img/two.svg">
			<p>A room is covered in hooks and pieces of fabric are strung between them, creating an over-arching shape. Placed through out this structure are subtle stimulations for the viewer's senses.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="one-third column add-bottom">
			<h3>The Shape-Builder</h3>
			<img class="one-third column" src="img/threeDark.svg">
			<p>I developed custom software in order to be able to design a shape specific to the exhibition space. The app allows users to build complex shapes using 3/4 sided polygons and outputs them as construction plans.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="one-third column add-bottom">
			<h3>Specific Objects</h3>
			<img class="one-third column" src="img/one.svg">
			<p>I have been greatly influenced by Donald Judd's idea of Specific Objects in creating this installation. In Judd's words: <em>"Three dimensions are real space. That gets rid of the problem of illusionism and of literal space, space in and around marks and colours."</em></p>
		</div>
